      options: [{ id: `A`, text: `&ldquo;It would be hard to overstate how useful California&rsquo;s irrigation infrastructure is today, as it remains the leading means of moving water for farming.&rdquo;` }, { id: `B`, text: `&ldquo;Natural humidity, which makes irrigation unnecessary or less important in California&rsquo;s northern reaches, falls off steadily toward the sun-scorched yet fertile valleys of the state&rsquo;s south.&rdquo;` }, { id: `C`, text: `&ldquo;A modern method, sprinkler irrigation sprays water in every direction using machinery; it is common across the United States and especially widespread in California.&rdquo;` }, { id: `D`, text: `&ldquo;Though simple, the irrigation system the Hohokam people built in 7th-century-CE Arizona used hydraulic-engineering features still relied on across California today.&rdquo;` }],
